<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The document status feature helps applicants monitor the progress of their requests from submission to final approval.</p>



<div class="wp-block-kadence-column kadence-column1845_efd09b-c9"><div class="kt-inside-inner-col"><h2 class="kt-adv-heading1845_f8a43c-c0 wp-block-kadence-advancedheading kt-adv-heading-has-icon has-theme-palette1-color has-text-color" data-kb-block="kb-adv-heading1845_f8a43c-c0"><span class="kb-svg-icon-wrap kb-adv-heading-icon kb-svg-icon-fas_hand-point-right kb-adv-heading-icon-side-left"><svg viewBox="0 0 512 512"  fill="currentColor" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"  aria-hidden="true"><path d="M512 199.652c0 23.625-20.65 43.826-44.8 43.826h-99.851c16.34 17.048 18.346 49.766-6.299 70.944 14.288 22.829 2.147 53.017-16.45 62.315C353.574 425.878 322.654 448 272 448c-2.746 0-13.276-.203-16-.195-61.971.168-76.894-31.065-123.731-38.315C120.596 407.683 112 397.599 112 385.786V214.261l.002-.001c.011-18.366 10.607-35.889 28.464-43.845 28.886-12.994 95.413-49.038 107.534-77.323 7.797-18.194 21.384-29.084 40-29.092 34.222-.014 57.752 35.098 44.119 66.908-3.583 8.359-8.312 16.67-14.153 24.918H467.2c23.45 0 44.8 20.543 44.8 43.826zM96 200v192c0 13.255-10.745 24-24 24H24c-13.255 0-24-10.745-24-24V200c0-13.255 10.745-24 24-24h48c13.255 0 24 10.745 24 24zM68 368c0-11.046-8.954-20-20-20s-20 8.954-20 20 8.954 20 20 20 20-8.954 20-20z"/></svg></span><span class="kb-adv-text-inner">TNREGINET Document Status Explained</span></h2></div></div>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The following table explains the most common status messages shown on TNREGINET.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-table is-style-stripes"><table class="has-background has-border-color has-theme-palette-11-border-color has-fixed-layout" style="background-color:#13612f80;border-width:3px"><thead><tr><th class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Status</th><th class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Meaning</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Pending</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Application received but not yet reviewed</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Processing</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Verification and review are in progress</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Approved</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Application successfully completed</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Returned</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Corrections or additional details required</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Rejected</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Application not approved due to errors</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Payment Pending</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Fee payment not completed or confirmed</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Completed</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Document is ready for use or download</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Understanding these statuses can help you determine the next action required.</p>



